							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello all, 
<br />

<br />
new on the board, I m a 18 bard on Storm (french server)...
<br />
First off all..thx for putting this great site+forum up!!
<br />

<br />
Now, sorry to bring the Troub vs Dirge debate on the table again, but after scanning most of the threads, I feel that one of the key issue (is that the case ?): Life tap vs power tap, is not talked about that much. It would be great if some of you experienced players could give some more information on this issue.
<br />
- are the tap big enough to make a difference, wether its life or power ?
<br />
- can u drain enuff to make a mob left with zero power during a fight, in group, or solo ?
<br />
- I feel this is a key issue... why ?? because both have CC after all, both have buff/debuff, both have damage, so besides rez on one side and regen on the other side, the true difference lies there: draining life or power. Do you think it is the case ?
<br />

<br />
Btw, apart from having a funny name, I'm leaning toward Troub cuz of the power tap, would go Dirge otherwise  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="Twisted Evil" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Way toooo long for a first post, sry  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> and thx in advance for the tons of answers that gonna flow in  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="Rolling Eyes" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
