						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm only a fledgeling Troub myself, only made 20 2 nights ago, so I'm definitely not an authority on the subject, but I will offer my opnion and take on the issue, and why I chose to be a Troub (aside from the RP reason).
<br />

<br />
The way I see it, a Troub will never get a mob's power down to zero with his power taps, same as a Dirge won't kill one with his lifetaps. The reason is that the taps don't so a large enough % of damage relative to a typical fight length (a fight would have to last very long for the wee taps to do it).
<br />

<br />
So what do the taps give you and your group? 
<br />

<br />
To the Troub, they give back some power. More power is translated to more CA', more Buffs/debuffs, ability to do emergency CC or taunting off a healer etc.
<br />

<br />
To the Dirge, they give healing, thus sparing (slightly) the group healer's power if the dirge is under attack, but have little else benefit for the group.
<br />

<br />
Now, consider your role and playstyle. Do you group more, or prefer to solo?
<br />

<br />
If you're more of a solo type, Dirge would seem the better choice, as it can provide a sort of mini built-in healer for you (what good is a full power bar when you die, eh?).
<br />

<br />
If you're more of a group person, the I see Troub as a way to go, because it can offer more in the way of group support.
<br />

<br />
BUT - All this 'analysis' pertains only to the question you have raised: lifetap vs powertap. There are several more distinguishes between the 2 subclasses which may of course affect your choice in the end.
<br />

<br />
Whatever you choose - choose because you think YOU will have fun playing, not because someone else tells you class x is uber and class y is gimped. In the end, you're here to do what YOU find fun, not what other people think. (As long as your fun doesn't involve griefing others, that goies without saying).
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps a bit &lt;smiles&gt;<br />_________________<br />Paitaan, 20th season Troubadour
<br />
Antonya Bayle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
