						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It also varies with the TYPE of group you normally join.  The healer I work with the most is a mystic and while a mystic is fine at keeping people alive, they are big on protection in the form of runes and less so with actual damage healing.  As such, health taps are easily as useful to our groups as power taps.
<br />

<br />
At this stage (lvl 23) I don't have taps yet, but I agree on the solo analysis -- I seldom run my power bar dry, at least fighting singles of the blue-to-yellow level, and what I end up waiting on for the next fight is health points.  It isn't a big difference, but I do think health regen is more significant solo than power.
<br />

<br />
But I really do think the differences, at least so far, are more subtle and not categorical.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.mausturm.com/EQ2/images/dingsig1.jpg"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
