						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You need to consider the general effect on the mob &amp; the effect on you:
<br />

<br />
-effect on mob
<br />
Lifetap will generally kill a mob faster, when it loses its life its dead jim. But high end mobs (dragons etc...) use their power to heal themselves, and often will not die until they first run out of power.  You can dmg them alot forcing them to heal themselves....or you can just get rid of the power directly
<br />

<br />
-effect on you
<br />
Lifetap will keep you alive longer, if you are taking damage. In a balanced group its not your job to take damage so healing yourself won't do much good. While soloing you take all of the damage so an extra heal is a good thing.
<br />

<br />
Powertap will give you more options as to what abilites you can use during a long fight. But long fights only occur against big mobs, mobs you usually fight in groups.
<br />

<br />
conclusion:
<br />
lifetap is better if you plan on doing alot of soloing
<br />
powertap is better if you plan on doing alot of grouping
<br />

<br />
BUT...this is only one difference between the classes</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
