							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The power taps are a little better for groups while life taps are better for soloing.  In a solo battle at lvl 30 I get around 200-300 pts in heals by doing my two life taps occassionally -- not too shabby.   In a group this doesn't matter as much except against AoEing mobs. 
<br />

<br />
Conversely, a power tap won't do you as much good soloing, but are handy when in groups to keep your power up.   You might be able to get an extra skill or two off without dipping low in power -- though I'm not sure how good those power taps are.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
