							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well I know you have your answer... but you should have read the troubador FAQ.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="Sad" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Power taps don't seem to be taps... they seem to be drains.  most of us troubs agree that we never see power going UP... just down.
<br />

<br />
I am lvl 37 now.. and if I want to power drain a mob to 0% I can.... it's nice... but doesn't come in very handy very often... it will probably be uber on raids though.... I notice it makes a much bigger difference on named high lvl mobs.
<br />

<br />
If it RETURNED the power like they say it does... then it would be handy all the time when grouping because I frequently run lower in power than other group members.
<br />

<br />
Lifetaps are handy when soloing... because not only does it give you HP to keep you healed without using a concentration slot (troubador HP regn takes 2 and is weak regen) but if give you a single "pool" to get to 0%  This means by spamming your HP tap abailities rather than power tap abilities you kill the mob faster which means the fights are shorter so you need less HP when soloing.
<br />

<br />
I want my power taps to return the mana to me... but I am not unhappy as a troubador.... I love my class.<br />_________________<br />Claire Dangermouse
