							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">At 32 my health taps give me about 70 hp back  (adept 1 of both spells)  it's nice, but with mobs doing 100+dmg a hit it's not much.  This comes from watching the little green numbers over my head.  I don't get a message that I was healed
<br />

<br />
As for the power taps, have you considered that you don't see your power going up because the cost of using the skill is more power than what the tap gives you back?   Your power would still go down, but more slowly.  Still allowing you to get a few extra hits in. 
<br />

<br />
I like my health taps.  Every once in awhile I get smacked, usually not a lot but I can heal myself up while my healer focuses on the tank.  And many of my skills have a power drain as well.  Best of both worlds.<br />_________________<br />Twists - 32 Dirge - 28 Tailor
